2026-01-05 19:58 ET - News Release
Mr. Dustin Henderson reports
BLACK MAMMOTH METALS ACQUIRES TOM'S PEDIMENT GOLD-SILVER PROPERTY, NV AND FINDS GEOPHYSICAL TARGET
Black Mammoth Metals Corp. has acquired the Tom's Pediment gold-silver property by staking 87 unpatented lode claims on lands administered by the Bureau of Land Management covering approximately 727 hectares (1,797 acres) located in the South Ravenswood mining district, Lander county, Nevada, and has completed a pole-dipole induced polarization survey with an interpreted inversion model.
IP results
The IP results confirm a target area at Tom where the chargeability high covers 2.3 square kilometres approximately (open northwest), and is coincident with a prominent gravity high and a resistivity high. The east-west IP lines (six) were spaced from 200 to 800 metres.
The Tom geophysical target is interpreted as down-dropped host lithologies in the pediment that correspond to the southeast extension of the Skookum trend with known gold, silver and copper mineralization in the South Ravenswood mountain range. The Skookum trend area is adjacent to the property, near the historic Maloy gold and silver mine, where Cretaceous granodiorite crops out and intrudes Paleozoic sedimentary strata, including the lower-plate Roberts Mountain and upper-plate Valmy Formations with gold mineralization occurring in the Paleozoic strata
   and in the granodiorite. Carbonate rocks of the Roberts Mountains formation are exposed below the Roberts Mountains thrust. Mineralization hosted on adjacent and/or nearby properties is not necessarily indicative of mineralization hosted on the company's property.
Based on the known alteration and mineralization styles in the South Ravenswood mountain range, the company will evaluate the IP-anomalous gravity anomalies in the pediment with exploration models which include detached and down-dropped, as well as potentially epithermal-type, mineralization zones distal and higher level to the exposed intrusive mineralization roots.
Exploration status
The geophysical target at Tom is ready for drill testing after a BLM notice of intent is complete.
Acquisition terms (U.S. dollars)
The company owns Tom's Pediment property 100 per cent with no finders' fees, royalties, share compensation or other terms in connection with the acquisition.
The company continues to acquire non-core exploration interests in the western United Stats by purchase or staking.
